parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized shoulder harness can lead to inadequate restraint of the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The motorized shoulder harnesses fail to move when the door is opened
the shoulder strap tightens around the neck and shoulders
the automatic shoulder restraints are positioned in an improper location
the harness pulls up against the neck and face of front occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to inadequate restraint of the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch
the buckle/latch plate inserts do not lock into the buckle
the seat belt buckle is cracked and pieces fall off
making the seatbelt unusable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to retract properly can lead to inadequate restraint of the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract
the lap/shoulder belt over-tightens and cannot be released
the seat belts fit poorly
applying extreme pressure to the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts down while driving
sometimes restarting after a few minutes
and other times taking a day to restart; no error codes are displayed on the car's computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sliding door can cause inconvenience and discomfort for passengers, and potentially lead to safety issues if the door does not close properly.
symptoms: The sliding door does not close all the way
requiring manual tightening; children have difficulty closing the door; headaches are experienced by passengers due to fumes entering the vehicle when the door is shut and windows are up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust manifold failure can cause fumes to leak into the passenger compartment, posing a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: A hole in the exhaust manifold causes fumes to leak into the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A short circuit in the wiring harness from the battery to the firewall can cause an under-hood fire, potentially leading to engine damage, vehicle damage, or even personal injury.
symptoms: Under-hood fire
burning smell
smoke emanating from the engine compartment
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU module can cause a complete engine shut down, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
loss of power
engine warning lights or error messages
sudden loss of acceleration.
